Active Staking Rewards (ASR)

Active Staking Rewards is an innovative way to reward active participants with JUP, allowing them to accrue more voting power over-time, in the simplest way possible.

Read more

What's in ASR Pool?

These are the tokens distributed for this ASR period. 0.75% of projects launched on the LFG Launchpad + 50M JUP from JUP's usage of the LFG Launchpad.

When claiming your JUP, it will be added to your stake. The rest of the tokens are distributed spot.

ASR Recap & Explainer

FAQ

Jupiter's community of cadets, voters, and users is huge and diverse. ASR functions as a bootstrapping mechanism to incentivize Jupiter's community to be involved in decisions, voting, and discussions.

It is an innovative reward system that rewards voters based on voting activity and community participation.
ASR Pool consists of the 0.75% LFG Launchpad fee, and 100M JUP from JUP's usage of the LFG Launchpad.

The 100M JUP is distributed across 2 quarters, with the first being this ASR Claim. In addition to the 50M JUP, we have CLOUD this period.
We distributed the ASR Pool of rewards equally across 9 proposals. For each proposal, your reward would be (Your Voting Power/Total Voting Power) * Reward per Proposal.

Basically, you get more rewards if you vote more times, or with more JUP each time. Read more
If you have an ongoing unstake, you will need to wait for it to complete or cancel the unstake before claiming your JUP rewards.

All JUP will be automatically added to your stake account after claiming. These stake accounts are viewable on vote.jup.ag.
ASR has been extended for another year, the next ASR Claim will be in the middle of January, containing $DBR and 50M JUP tokens.
